In his weekly address, President Trump gives an update on the work his administration has accomplished in its first week. He highlights meetings with leaders of manufacturing companies and labor unions, emphasizing his goal of keeping jobs in America. He mentions several executive actions, including preparing for the repeal and replacement of Obamacare, withdrawing from the Trans-Pacific Partnership, beginning construction of the Keystone and Dakota Access pipelines with a requirement for American steel, expediting permits for infrastructure and manufacturing plants, and starting the border wall and cracking down on sanctuary cities. The president concludes by expressing his commitment to fighting for the American people.